children.subject:
There is not actually a thing as "denied from being added from the waitlist".

As a third-year CS major, I assume you're already familiar with the unchanged* CS enrollment policies from past years.

* other than the no purge change

Email regarding waitlist (CS 162)

Hi, I am aware of the 70% rule, but after being added to the waitlist for 162, I got this email:

I was wondering if this is regarding the 70% rule, or was I denied from being added from the waitlist. I am currently a third-year CS major. Thanks!

CS170 undeclared Enrollment Update

Does this mean that there is no way for me to get into the class? Do I need a code? Or simply that I have to wait until the class is open to all majors during the adjustment period?

Enrolling in CS 170/CS 188

Hi, I'm a CS-intended transfer student taking my remaining CS lower div reqs right now: 61A, 70, 16A (with exception of 16B). I'm relatively new to Berkeley class enrollment, so I was wondering what the email below means for my enrollment in 170 and 188. Will I be able to take them, why or why not? Also, is there anything I can do about this? Additionally, will declaring CS later make a difference in getting in?

189 enrollment email

I just got this email. I'm confused however because I am majoring in EECS, and the course description for 189 says that 280 seats are reserved for EECS/CS majors.

Reserved seat requirements

I received an email yesterday that I do not meet the reserved seat requirements for CS 161, even though I am declared. I am currently in CS 61C, a prereq for the class, so is that the reason for the email? If not, does anyone know why?

Declared CS do not meet any requirements for the reserved seats?

I just got an email says: 

Class: COMPSCI   189 

Section: 001

Reason: Available seats are reserved and you do not meet any requirements for the reserved seats.

You will remain on the wait list until a seat for which you qualify opens.

Should I worry about this?

history.content:
It appears that once students are waitlisted, you're getting automated messages from the Registrar. No need to email them to us, and also we are not the ones sending them. It doesn't mean that you won't be enrolled off the waitlisted - it's just wordly poorly and means you're currently on the waitlist at this time, and have not yet been enrolled in the course...because you're on the waitlist for the various reasons according to our enrollment policies. See below:

Please first read 

https://piazza.com/class/hyq0br1u3kx7dg?cid=5205 for CS Lower Divs

https://piazza.com/class/hyq0br1u3kx7dg?cid=5203 for CS Upper divs

https://piazza.com/class/hyq0br1u3kx7dg?cid=5172 for EE 16A/B

Please also read our enrollment policies: 

https://eecs.berkeley.edu/resources/undergrads/cs/degree-reqs/enrollment-policy  CS enrollment policy

https://eecs.berkeley.edu/resources/undergrads/eecs/degree-reqs/enrollment-policy EE enrollment policy

TL:DR Certain categories of students will be able to directly enroll into classes. Non-majors are waitlisted for CS classes. CS upper divs cap enrollment at 70% regardless of major status.
